<br>
Can people work with the Warrior to make a situation viable? Certainly, no arguement, they absolutely can.  There is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>always</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a way to make a Warrior work.  However, it's much like pulling a plow yourself.  Using a Knight is much like hooking a horse up to the plow.  People are going to prefer the Knight because they're less work.  They require less thought on everyone's part.  The only one who might maybe have to do a little more thinking is the Cleric, and if they aren't having to heal anyone other than the Knight, it's a hell of a lot easier than the alternative, so they're okay with it too.<br>
<br>
Never under estimate the power of human laziness.<br>
<br>
