<br>
Think about when a shaman or enchanter slow a mob and then gets aggro. Well the mob is now doing about 1/4 the damage it did before - so that enchanter or shaman tanks a slowed mob better than you tank an unslowed mob. No biggie though, any smart shaman or enchanter isn't going to sit or throw out a lot of nukes or dots right after slowing. Just taunt and melee and most of the time you'll piggyback the aggro off the slow (when taunt succeeds).<br>
<br>
If slow aggro is a huge problem and taunt failed, try AE taunt or /shield. I usually go for /shield if slow stuck and AE taunt if it was resisted.<br>
<br>
Now the damage dealer classes are another type of aggro entirely, and this is where knights really shine... Knight aggro spells are pretty much like our high aggro weapon procs, but they only need mana for these, we need luck...<br>
<br>
And yes, people do often just want to play lazy. Nuke whenever they want, sit whenever they want, never have to turn off attack (god forbid, but they hate it). <br>
<br>
Anyone that tells you to taunt more is going further than just being lazy, now they just don't understand how warriors get aggro. Yep, I'm sitting here without aggro laughing at you while taunt has been up for almost a minute /sigh. There are lots of people in this game who don't have a clue how a class other than their own works though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aveenlucenthawk>Aveen Lucenthawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 154<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/03 12:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2872.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Aggro</span><hr size=1> My sister plays a rogue and we often play opposite together. When I or another warrior tank, she has to evade every chance she gets, turn off attack, and even switch weapons. She doesn't want to work this hard to not tank -- no one does.<br>
<br>
With a knight she doesn't have to work that hard. <br>
<br>
This facet of human nature (taking the easiest way out) coupled with the fact that warriors have only one job (tanking which is the superset containing agro control) is the chief cause of a lot of grief for a lot of warriors just trying to have some fun in an exp group. <p>Aveen Lucenthawk<br>
